## Special Blocks and Alerts

### Information Blocks

> **Information**: SlideLang v3.0 includes more than 40 native integrations with popular enterprise tools such as Salesforce, HubSpot, Slack, Microsoft 365, and Google Workspace.

> **Tip**: For executive presentations, limit each slide to a maximum of 3 main points. The "3x3" rule (3 slides, 3 points, 3 minutes) is ideal for capturing attention.

> **Key Fact**: 68% of executives make decisions within the first 30 seconds of a presentation. Visual formatting is crucial in that critical window.

### Warning Blocks

> **Warning**: During the initial content migration, we recommend running parallel systems for 2-3 weeks to ensure operational continuity and allow for rollback if needed.

> **Attention**: Changes to global variables affect every presentation that uses them. Always back up before modifying master templates.

> **Caution**: When using advanced formatting, verify compatibility with all output formats (PDF, PowerPoint, HTML). Some elements may require specific adjustments.

### Success Blocks

> **Success**: Our 2,800 beta users report 94% average satisfaction and a 78% improvement in content creation productivity.

> **Achievement**: Implementation completed under budget and ahead of schedule. All systems are operating within expected parameters, and KPIs exceed targets.

> **Result**: Adopting SlideLang delivered a 340% ROI in the first year, surpassing initial projections of 250%.

### Error and Problem Blocks

> **Error**: Incompatibility detected with legacy versions of Internet Explorer. We recommend updating to modern browsers or using specific fallbacks.

> **Known Issue**: PDF export may show minor differences with custom fonts. We use system fonts as an automatic fallback.

> **Issue**: Some users report latency in real-time collaboration with teams larger than 50 people. We're optimizing performance for Q2 2025.

